To prove that $↑(A \setminus \{a\}) \sim ↑(B \setminus \{b\})$, we need to show that the set difference $A \setminus \{a\}$ is equivalent to $B \setminus \{b\}$ under the function $f$ restricted to $A \setminus \{a\}$.

