Since $f$ is surjective from $A$ to $B$, for any $y \in B$, there is some $x \in A$ such that $f(x) = y$. If $y \in B \setminus \{b\}$, then $y \neq b$. If $x = a$, then $f(a) = b$, so $y \neq f(a)$. Thus $x \neq a$, so $x \in A \setminus \{a\}$.

